ğŸš€ 3. How to Run (Flask Version)

Step 1 â€” Create data/ directory
Create the data/ directory and place your key files (embeddings.npy, metadata.csv, nn_model.joblib) inside it.

Step 2 â€” Install dependencies

pip install -r requirements.txt


Step 3-5 â€” (Optional) Data Pipeline
If you need to regenerate your data:

python fetch_from_excel_playwright.py
python clean_catalog.py
python build_index.py


Step 6 â€” (Optional) Run retrieval test (CLI)

python retrieve_test.py


Step 7 â€” Run the Flask App (Locally)

flask run --port 8000


Or for development with auto-reload:

FLASK_ENV=development flask run --port 8000


Open http://127.0.0.1:8000 in your browser.

Step 8 â€” Run for Production (How Render will run it)
Render will use this command (defined in your requirements.txt).

gunicorn app:app


